<Link id="l00230" /><CodeLine lineNumber="230"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00231" /><CodeLine lineNumber="231"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00232" /><CodeLine lineNumber="232"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Do the access attribute and DSOLocal propagation in combined index.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00233" /><CodeLine lineNumber="233"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The goal of attribute propagation is internalization of readonly (RO)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00234" /><CodeLine lineNumber="234"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// or writeonly (WO) variables. To determine which variables are RO or WO</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00235" /><CodeLine lineNumber="235"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// and which are not we take following steps:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00236" /><CodeLine lineNumber="236"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - During analysis we speculatively assign readonly and writeonly</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00237" /><CodeLine lineNumber="237"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   attribute to all variables which can be internalized. When computing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00238" /><CodeLine lineNumber="238"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   function summary we also assign readonly or writeonly attribute to a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00239" /><CodeLine lineNumber="239"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   reference if function doesn&#39;t modify referenced variable (readonly)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00240" /><CodeLine lineNumber="240"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   or doesn&#39;t read it (writeonly).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00241" /><CodeLine lineNumber="241"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00242" /><CodeLine lineNumber="242"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - After computing dead symbols in combined index we do the attribute</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00243" /><CodeLine lineNumber="243"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   and DSOLocal propagation. During this step we:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00244" /><CodeLine lineNumber="244"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   a. clear RO and WO attributes from variables which are preserved or</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00245" /><CodeLine lineNumber="245"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      can&#39;t be imported</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00246" /><CodeLine lineNumber="246"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   b. clear RO and WO attributes from variables referenced by any global</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00247" /><CodeLine lineNumber="247"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      variable initializer</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00248" /><CodeLine lineNumber="248"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   c. clear RO attribute from variable referenced by a function when</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00249" /><CodeLine lineNumber="249"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      reference is not readonly</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00250" /><CodeLine lineNumber="250"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   d. clear WO attribute from variable referenced by a function when</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00251" /><CodeLine lineNumber="251"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      reference is not writeonly</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00252" /><CodeLine lineNumber="252"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   e. clear IsDSOLocal flag in every summary if any of them is false.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00253" /><CodeLine lineNumber="253"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00254" /><CodeLine lineNumber="254"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   Because of (c, d) we don&#39;t internalize variables read by function A</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00255" /><CodeLine lineNumber="255"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   and modified by function B.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00256" /><CodeLine lineNumber="256"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00257" /><CodeLine lineNumber="257"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Internalization itself happens in the backend after import is finished</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00258" /><CodeLine lineNumber="258"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// See internalizeGVsAfterImport.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00259" /><CodeLine lineNumber="259" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/modulesummaryindex/#a9429ff234f880cabe578772a233553c5"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/modulesummaryindex/#a9429ff234f880cabe578772a233553c5">ModuleSummaryIndex::propagateAttributes</a>(</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00260" /><CodeLine lineNumber="260"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/denseset">DenseSet&lt;GlobalValue::GUID&gt;</a> &amp;GUIDPreservedSymbols) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00261" /><CodeLine lineNumber="261"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!<a href="#ab725626efcb99210464e7e355171a21f">PropagateAttrs</a>)</span></CodeLine>
